France, Germany in ‘Intensive’ Talks on Bolstering Rescue Fund

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-10-18T19:44:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/france-germany-in-intensive-talks-on-bolstering-rescue-fund.html
France and  Germany  are engaged in
“intensive talks” on bolstering the European Financial
Stability Facility, Steffen Seibert, German  Chancellor Angela
Merkel ’s chief spokesman, said today. He declined in an
interview to comment on a report in the Guardian that they
reached agreement on increasing the size of the fund, saying he
won’t comment on intermediate results of the negotiations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
